def remove_word(text, word):
    return text.replace(word, "")
print(remove_word("Hello world!", "world")) 
# Output: Hello! 
This function takes two parameters, `text` and `word`, and returns the text with all occurrences of the word removed. The `replace()` method in Python replaces all occurrences of a substring with another substring. In this case, it replaces all occurrences of the word with an empty string, effectively removing them.
